query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `spectrumSnapshots` (
  `id` int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `userId` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `frequency` bigint NOT NULL,
  `sampleRate` bigint NOT NULL,
  `gain` int NOT NULL,
  `signalType` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `peakPower` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `noiseFloor` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `snr` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `bandwidth` bigint DEFAULT NULL,
  `confidence` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `metadata` text,
  `source` enum('manual','auto','scan') DEFAULT 'auto',
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_frequency` (`frequency`),
  KEY `idx_userId` (`userId`),
  KEY `idx_createdAt` (`createdAt`)
);
